# Customer Risk Analysis Using SQL

## Project Overview

This project analyzes customer financial behavior using SQL to identify potential high-risk customers. The analysis focuses on customer balance, income levels, complaint frequency, and customer segments to detect patterns that may indicate financial risk or dissatisfaction.

The objective is to demonstrate how SQL can be used to perform business analysis and generate insights that support decision-making in financial services or customer management environments.

---

## Business Problem

Organizations need to identify customers who may present financial or service risks. Customers with unusually low balances, high complaint counts, or behavior that deviates from their segment averages may indicate potential churn or financial instability.

This project aims to:

* Analyze customer financial metrics
* Compare individual customers against their segment averages
* Identify customers who may require attention or further investigation

---

## Dataset Description

The dataset contains customer-level financial and behavioral information.

| Column           | Description                                       |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------------- |
| CustomerID       | Unique identifier for each customer               |
| Customer Segment | Customer classification group                     |
| Balance          | Current balance maintained by the customer        |
| Income           | Annual income of the customer                     |
| NumComplaints    | Total number of complaints raised by the customer |

The dataset allows comparison between individual customer performance and segment-level benchmarks.

---

## SQL Analysis

The SQL query calculates average balance and income for each customer segment. Individual customer values are then compared with these averages to identify deviations.

The analysis helps detect customers whose financial behavior differs significantly from their segment norms.

Key SQL concepts used in this project include:

* Aggregation functions (AVG)
* Group By operations
* Common Table Expressions (CTE)
* Conditional comparisons
* Data segmentation analysis

---

## Key Insights

The analysis reveals several useful patterns:

• Customers with balances significantly below their segment average may represent financial risk.
• Customers with high complaint counts may indicate dissatisfaction or potential churn.
• Segment comparison helps identify outliers in financial behavior.
• Combining financial metrics with behavioral indicators improves risk identification.

These insights can help businesses prioritize customer engagement, improve service quality, and mitigate potential risks.

